  "title": "Service Engineer (Plastic Injection)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Drive the expansion of the engineering plastics business in ASEAN and India by applying deep technical industry knowledge and data.</li>\n  <li>Deliver comprehensive technical solutions, including part design analysis (CAE), tooling, injection molding</li>\n  <li>Investigate the mechanical and physical properties of materials using scientific instruments for new product development.</li>\n  <li>Provide technical data, competitor comparisons, and post-sales advisory to support commercial activities.</li>\n  <li>Conduct failure analysis, benchmark testing, and defect investigation through various testing methods.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Polymer Science/Engineering or a related field.</li>\n  <li>Mandatory knowledge of Polymer/Plastics technology.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of experience in plastics injection molding and chemical analysis.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click on the APPLY button below to send in your resume.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No: 13C6305</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Reg. No.: R22104949 KOH SHI MIN, JOAN (XU SHIMIN)</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>For candidates who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p>",
